{{Infobox journal | title = Evolution & Development | cover = Evolution and development cover.gif | editor = Rudolf A. Raff | discipline = [[Biology]] | abbreviation = Evol. Dev. | publisher = [[Wiley-Blackwell]] | country = | frequency = | history = 1999-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 3.179 | impact-year = 2009 | website = http://www.wiley.com/bw/journal.asp?ref=1520-541x | link1 = http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/118546131/home?CRETRY=1&SRETRY=0 | link1-name = Online access | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 41390326 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 1520-541X | eISSN = 1525-142X }} '''''Evolution & Development''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] publishing material at the interface of [[evolutionary biology|evolutionary]] and [[developmental biology]]. Within [[evolutionary developmental biology]], it has the aim of aiding a broader synthesis of biological thought in these two areas. Its scope ranges from [[paleontology]] and [[population biology]], to developmental and [[molecular biology]], including [[mathematics]] and the [[history of science|history]] and [[philosophy of science]].
It was established in 1999 by five biologists: [[Wallace Arthur]], [[Sean B. Carroll]], Michael Coates, [[Rudolf Raff]], and Gregory Wray. They continue to serve as editors.<ref name=board>{{cite web |url=http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/118546131/home/EditorialBoard.html |title=Wiley InterScience :: JOURNALS :: Evolution & Development |work= |accessdate=2009-11-26}}</ref> It is published by [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the [[Society for Integrative and Comparative Biology]].
