'''Geoffroy d'Ablis''' was a [[Dominican Order|Dominican]] who led the [[Inquisition]] in [[Carcassonne]] against [[Catharism|Cathars]] such as [[Peire Autier]] from 1303 to 1316.<ref>{{cite book|last=O'Shea|first=Stephen|title=The Friar Of Carcassonne|year=2011|publisher=Douglas & McIntyre|isbn=978-1-55365-551-0|pages=xvii}}</ref> He collaborated with [[Bernard Gui]], the inquisitor at [[Toulouse]].

