'''Huang Dao''' ({{zh|黄道}}; April 25, 1900 – May 23, 1939) original name Huang Duanzhang ({{zh|黄端章}}), also known as Yiming ({{zh|一鸣}}) was a member of the [[Chinese Workers' and Peasants' Red Army]] and the [[New Fourth Army]]. He was born in [[Hengfeng County]], [[Jiangxi]] Province. He was the father of [[Huang Zhizhen]], who was governor of [[Hubei]] Province under the [[People's Republic of China]]. He fought in the [[Chinese Civil War]] on the side of the [[Communist Party of China]], being active in northern and eastern [[Fujian]] near the border with [[Zhejiang]]. He remained in [[southern China]] after the [[Long March]]. During the [[Second Sino-Japanese War]], he was poisoned by the [[Kuomintang]] en route to southern [[Anhui]].<ref>{{cite book|title=黄道传|author=陈群哲|year=2000|location=南昌|publisher=江西人民出版社|pages=19|isbn=7-210-02245-7}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=不朽的革命战士|editor=江西省民政厅|year=1960|publisher=江西人民出版社|pages=153|url=http://book.chaoxing.com/ebook/read_810323682e75593b48f3732f7825ec835cce485c0_153.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.rjjng.com.cn/research/2010/1411275444288.html|title =中华苏维埃共和国中央执行委员会布告|date =1934-02-03|accessdate=2015-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=《中国人民解放军军史》编写组|title=中国人民解放军军史：第一卷|year=2010|publisher=军事科学出版社|pages=443|isbn=978-7-80237-381-5}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=粟裕 |title=粟裕回忆录|year=2007 |publisher= 解放军出版社 |location=北京|isbn=978-7-5065-5426-8|pages=128}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://history.sohu.com/20140401/n397486092.shtml|title=粟裕曾设鸿门宴绑架开国上将 押送途中遇突袭|date=2014-04-01|accessdate=2015-02-24|publisher=搜狐}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=张明金、刘立勤 |title=中国人民解放军历史上的200个军区|year=2010|publisher=解放军文艺出版社 |location=北京|pages=61|isbn=978-7-5033-2252-5}}</ref>
