This is a list of people legally executed in Mexico. The [[Capital punishment|death penalty]] was a [[Capital punishment in Mexico|legal punishment in Mexico]] since [[Pre-Columbian era|Pre-Columbian times]], and was still applied during its contemporary history. The last non-military execution in Mexico was in 1937, and the last military execution was in 1961,<ref name="BBC2">{{Citation|title=Death penalty debate grows in Mexico|date=4 February 2009|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/7866811.stm|author=Gibbs, Stephen|publisher=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=2 August 2009}}</ref> with the civil death penalty being abolished in 1976 and the military death penalty in 2005. The next list is representative and includes people condemned and executed during Mexican history:
== Twentieth century == ===Civilian (until 1937)===
