aborer man who was condemned to death for the rape and murder of María de la Luz Margarita Mendoza Noriega, a 9 years-old girl. The 18 January 1957, in [[Hermosillo]], Sonora, Ruíz Corrales cheated to the girl by carried her to an isolated place where raped and strangled her. The victim sold tomatoes in a local market and several witnesses saw her to go with Ruíz Corrales, he was arrested the same day of the murder and was sentenced to capital punishment only one week after. He was executed together to José Rosario Zamarripa, other man condemned for similar crimes.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/entrada-de-opinion/colaboracion/mochilazo-en-el-tiempo/nacion/sociedad/2017/07/21/por-que-dejo-de|title=¿Pórque dejó de aplicarse la pena de muerte en México?|last=Delgadillo|first=Magalli|date=21 July 2017|work=El Universal|access-date=20 October 2017|location=Mexico City, Mexico|language=Spanish|trans-title=Why did it stop the application of death penalty in Mexico?}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archivo.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/48447.html|title=En 1957, los últimos ejecutados en el país|last=Beyliss|first=Marcelo|date=17 February 2017|work=El Universal|access-date=20 October 2017|location=Sonora, Mexico|language=Spanish|trans-title=In 1957, the last executed men in the country}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.expreso.com.mx/seccion/cultura/18191-a-60-anos-de-la-pena-de-muerte-en-mexico-ultima-ejecucion-fue-en-hermosillo.html|title=A 60 años de la pena de muerte en México; últim ejecución fue en Hermosillo|last=Barrios|first=Benjamín|date=17 June 2017|work=Expreso|access-date=20 October 2017|location=Sonora, Mexico|language=Spanish|trans-title=To 60 years of death penalty in Mexico; the last execution was in Hermosillo}}</ref> | |- |}
