{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}} {{Use British English|date=April 2016}} {{infobox football biography | name = Walter Brown | image = | fullname = Walter Ephraim Brown | height = | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | birth_date = 1867 | birth_place = [[Birmingham]], England | death_date = | years1 = | clubs1 = Soho Villa | years2 = | clubs2 = Grove Hill | years3 = | clubs3 = Hockley Belmont | years4 = | clubs4 = St James's | years5 = 1891 | clubs5 = [[Birmingham City F.C.|Small Heath]] | caps5 = 3 | goals5 = 2 | years6 = 1891–???? | clubs6 = [[Crosswell's Brewery F.C.|Crosswell's Brewery]] }} '''Walter Ephraim Brown''' (1867 – after 1890) was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played in the [[Football Alliance]] for [[Birmingham City F.C.|Small Heath]]. Brown was born in the [[Handsworth, West Midlands|Handsworth]] district of [[Birmingham]] and played football for several local clubs before spending a couple of months with Small Heath.<ref name=Matthews76>{{cite book |last=Matthews |first=Tony |title=Birmingham City: A Complete Record |year=1995 |publisher=Breedon Books |location=Derby |page=76 |isbn=978-1-85983-010-9}}</ref> He played in three of the first four games of the [[1891–92 Football Alliance]] season, once on the [[Outside forward|left wing]] and twice at [[inside left]], scoring in each of the latter two,<ref>Matthews, p. 141.</ref> before returning to local football with [[Crosswell's Brewery F.C.|Crosswell's Brewery]].<ref name=Matthews76/>
