{{other people|William Abbott}}
{{no footnotes|date=May 2011}}


'''William Abbott''' was a [[theatrical manager]], based in [[England]], and [[South Carolina]], United States.

He worked with the [[Haymarket Theatre]] in [[London]], later moving to [[Charleston, South Carolina]], where he created the [[New Charleston Theatre]] and operated it from 1837 through 1841.  This theatre brought theatrical stars like [[Ellen Tree]], Booth, Cooper, and Vandenhoff to Charleston.{{citation needed|date=May 2011}} He also maintained a repertory company there.

